The paper discusses a formalism for dependability modeling and evaluation, which involves both modeling and analysis. The use of parametric system modeling is investigated, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the state space explosion problem, which is a common issue in computer science (cs.CR). The use of probabilistic Horn abduction as a framework for analysis suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
